description:
Applications are invited from suitably qualified Malawians, Civil Servants or non-civil servants, as the case may be, depending on the requirements of the post, for the vacancies listed below existing in the Civil Service:

MINISTRY OF WATER AND SANITATION

Vac. 37/23

Post : Senior Community Water Supply Officer (Wells) (Grade H)

Salary: Within the Grade H salary scale segment

Location: Ministry of Water and Sanitation

Qualifications:

Applicants should be in possession of Bachelor of Science in Engineering in any of the fields: Civil Engineering, Water Engineering, Municipal/Water Utilities, Water Supply Engineering and water Resources Engineering obtained from accredited institutions.

Duties:

Facilitating the rehabilitation and reduction of unaccounted for water of existing water supply systems;

Supervising reticulated systems and water points maintenance and other water supply related infrastructure;

Facilitating collection of water point data in liaison with all... stakeholders and relevant authorities;

Ensuring that mitigation measures are undertaken for water points that are not providing potable water in terms of quantity and quality;

Preparing operation and maintenance guidelines for water points;

Monitoring implementation of water supply project activities;

Supervising duties of junior staff under him/her;

Facilitating availability and distribution of water supply plant spare parts;

Participating in planning and coordinating meeting on WASH issues at the district;

Facilitating implementation of capacity building activities (including trainings) for user communities of water supply and sanitation facilities;

Disseminating National Policies and guidelines on WASH;

Participating in advocacy campaigns for promoting proper use water supply sources; and

Participating in designing developing and revising policy documents on WASH.

Note:

Documentary evidence of major requirements specified in the advertisement shall be required during interviews. Serving officers will also be required to demonstrate during the interviews that they are permanent and pensionable officers in the Civil Service by producing letters of confirmation in appointment in addition to letters of condition of appointment on probation (PSR 19).

Civil Service Commission is an equal opportunity employer: All qualified individuals are welcome to apply. Interested qualified candidates should submit their applications together with copies of relevant Certificates and Curriculum Vitae to:-

The Secretary

Civil Service Commission

P.O. Box 30133

LILONGWE 3

Email: cservice@csc.gov.mw

To reach him not later than 14th April, 2023

Application email or URL: cservice@csc.gov.mw

