description:
The Lilongwe Water Board is a Statutory Corporation established in 1947 and re-constituted

under the Water Works Act (Cap 72). It is responsible for the provision of water supply services to the City of Lilongwe and other surrounding areas designated as its supply area. The Board is inviting applications from suitably qualified candidates of Malawian origin to fill the following TEMPORARY positions that exist within the Board.

PLUMBERS

Reporting to the Distribution Engineer, the Plumbers will be responsible for the following

Key duties and responsibilities:

2.1 Key Duties and Responsibilities

a) Undertaking routine and planned maintenance works in compliance with standards;

b) Installing new connections and geo referencing;

c) Undertaking leak detection exercise within the area;

d) Marking frequently bursting pipes within the area using Geographical Information System (GIS) and arrange replacement of the same;

e) Reporting all open trenches and road sections for... reinstatement after repair of faults;

f) Enforcing water board bye-laws;

g) Supervising and appraising staff under his/her care;

h) Participating in carrying out maintenance work on mains and supply pipes in emergencies and or when need arises;

i) Preparing reports;

j) Responding to queries on matters related to water supply aspects;

k) Monitoring resource utilization for maintenance works done in the area;

l) Building the capacity of Water supply in the area at all levels.

m) Implementing meter replacement programs;

n) Demonstrating outstanding commitment to service delivery programs of the Board by

personally identifying and reporting water bursts/leakages to customer care Division of

which verifiable repair records shall be tendered to be used as one of the components

for assessment during one’s performance appraisal time.

2.2 Minimum Qualification and Experience

A Minimum of a Malawi School Certificate of Education (MSCE) plus a Grade 1 Trade Test

Certificate/ level 3 TEVET Certificate in Plumbing from a recognised institution with two

(2) years’ experience in plumbing.

METHOD OF APPLICATION

All interested candidates who meet the above requirements should submit their

applications coupled with a detailed Curriculum Vitae and names and contact details of

three traceable referees not later than Friday, 13th October, 2023 to:

The Chief Executive Officer

Lilongwe Water Board

P.O Box 96

LILONGWE

Lilongwe Water Board is an Equal Opportunity Employer. Canvassing will Lead to Disqualification

